  ##Category B

  You can usually drive a vehicle and trailer with a combined weight of up to 8,250kg MAM (maximum authorised mass). View your driving licence information to check.

  You’re also allowed to drive a minibus with a trailer over 750kg MAM.

  ##Category BE test

  The size of the trailer depends on the BE ‘valid from’ date shown on your licence. If the date is:

  - before 19 January 2013, you can tow any size trailer within the towing limits of the vehicle
  - on or after 19 January 2013, you can tow a trailer within the towing limits of the vehicle with a MAM of up to 3,500kg

